We can perform cross-validation using `skm.GridSearchCV()`  to select the
best choice of $\gamma$ and `C` for an SVM with a radial
kernel:




::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
kfold = skm.KFold(5, 
                  random_state=0,
                  shuffle=True)
grid = skm.GridSearchCV(svm_rbf,
                        {'C':[0.1,1,10,100,1000],
                         'gamma':[0.5,1,2,3,4]},
                        refit=True,
                        cv=kfold,
                        scoring='accuracy');
grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
```

